Interface INaviAgentV1

All Superinterfaces:
Disposable, INavi
All Known Implementing Classes:
Navi
public interface INaviAgentV1 extends INavi
The Interface INaviAgentV1 defines methods for special interaction between BdiAgentV1 and the Navi.

  • Method Details

    • updateMapAndPathfind

      PathFindingResult[][] updateMapAndPathfind(String supervisor, String agent, int agentIndex, Point position, int vision, Set<massim.protocol.data.Thing> things, List<Point> goalPoints, List<Point> rolePoints, int step, String team, int maxSteps, int score, Set<massim.protocol.data.NormInfo> normsInfo, Set<massim.protocol.data.TaskInfo> taskInfo, List<Point> attachedPoints, List<Point> marker)
      Saves data from an agent received in the current step into the GameMap and starts path finding.
      Parameters:
      supervisor - the name of the supervisor of the group the agent is part of
      agent - the name of the agent
      agentIndex - the index of the agent
      position - the current position of the agent
      vision - the size of the vision of the agent
      things - the things which are currently in vision
      goalPoints - the goal points which are currently in vision
      rolePoints - the role points which are currently in vision
      step - the current step of the simulation
      team - the name of the team the agent is part of
      maxSteps - the number of steps the match has
      score - the current score of the team
      normsInfo - the current active norms
      taskInfo - the current active tasks
      attachedPoints - the attached points of the agent
      marker - the marker which are currently in vision
      Returns:
      a two dimensional Array of type PathFindingResult which contains information about distance and direction of certain interesting points.

    • updateAgentDebugData

      void updateAgentDebugData(String agent, String supervisor, String role, int energy, String lastAction, String lastActionSuccess, String lastActionIntention, String groupDesireType, String groupDesirePartner, String groupDesireBlock, String attachedThingsDebugString)
      Sends current agent data to the GraphicalDebugger.
      Parameters:
      agent - the name of the agent
      supervisor - the name of the supervisor of the group the agent is part of
      role - the name of the current role of the agent
      energy - the current energy of the agent
      lastAction - the name of the last action performed by the agent
      lastActionSuccess - an indicator if the last action was successful
      lastActionIntention - the name of the intention the last action came from
      groupDesireType - the name of the group desire the agent has in its desires
      groupDesirePartner - the name of the team mate which performs a group desire with the agent
      groupDesireBlock - the block on which the group desire is based on
      attachedThingsDebugString - a String containing information about the attached things of the agent
      See Also:
      • GraphicalDebugger

      String getDirectionToNearestUndiscoveredPoint(String supervisor, String agent, String lastMoveDirection)
      Gets the direction to the nearest undiscovered point in the GameMap.
      Parameters:
      supervisor - the name of the supervisor of the group the agent is part of
      agent - the name of the agent
